message_1: Find all prime numbers between 50 and 70, inclusive.
message_2:
To find all the prime numbers between 50 and 70, inclusive, we will check each number in this range to see if it has only two distinct factors: 1 and itself.

Here are the prime numbers between 50 and 70:

53: Factors are 1 and 53 (prime)
59: Factors are 1 and 59 (prime)
61: Factors are 1 and 61 (prime)
67: Factors are 1 and 67 (prime)

So, the prime numbers between 50 and 70, inclusive, are 53, 59, 61, and 67.
